gn=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xgoddessathenax>xGoddess Athenax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Wisdom and War</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/12/03 5:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/goddessathena1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Poseidon and the Erinyes</span><hr size=1> Those black occulars stared cold as Poseidon mention Hephaestus, the darkness with in soared. A plot would be in order...but not today. <br>
<br>
&quot;The time for honouring yourself will be at an end, Poseidon. Watch your back...or I'll be chewing on it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Athena feared none, she stood tall and proud. When the Furies made their appearance, those raven pools gave them a glance and a slight smile crossed her features. Her focus returned to the leaving Poseidon. Now I know hwere Hypnos won his arrogance, she thought to herself. This quarrel affected more than just Poseidon and Athena. For Hephaestus had ATTEMPTED to rape Athena, but instead only Gaia was ravaged.<br>
<br>
She was infact, Zeus's favored. Nothing could ever changed that. Zeus was rightfully King of the Gods, anything that happened he could rule over. <p>_.- Goddess Athena, Goddess of Wisdom, War, the arts, and crafts -._<br>
&quot;Think to yourself that everyday is your last; the hour to which you do not look foward will come as a welcome suprise...&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=poseidonkofc>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/12/03 9:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theoi.com/image/K2.1Poseidon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poseidon and the Erinyes</span><hr size=1> At the appearance of the Erinyes the sea god almost shook with fear and he eyed them warily as they asked him what he was doing. He figured they were acting to be ignorant of the thing that just occured between him and Athena. Stealing a glance to Zeus' favorite, Poseidon said to the Erinyes, &quot;No, nothing much going on here. I just caught Athena as I was headed out and paid her my condolances.&quot; He grinned as he played along with their seeming ignorance. <br>
<br>
Athena shot back at Poseidon after he had spoken to the three sisters and the god laughed in arrogance. &quot;Athena, my back is always watched. None on Olympus or on the wide carpets of the earth, not even your brother Apollo can hold their own in battle with me for long. None but your father that is. And with himn I have no quarrel. Try not to run to daddy in tears over our problems Athena.&quot; At that Poseidon took the hand of each Erinye and in succession gave them a kiss on their cheek before he left the great hall. <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/14/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poseidon and the Erinyes</span><hr size=1> Alecto rolled her eyes as Poseidon left. She then turned her gaze to Athena.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let his pressence not trouble you young Goddess. If we find out that he truly did have anything to do with what Hepheastus did, he shall pay for eternity.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera and Tisiphone nodded in agreement. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">~*~ Jessica ~*~<br>
