<br>
She turned to the Furies, and smiled. She moved to Alecto's side, staring at where Poseidon made his disgusting exit. &quot;I know he was behind it. But justice be fair. Unfortunately.&quot; <br>
<br>
Those dark occulars turned to Demeter, &quot;Dear Aunt, it <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>has</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> been too long. How do you fair?&quot; Athena did a slight bow to greet the Seasons Goddess. <p>_.- Goddess Athena, Goddess of Wisdom, War, the arts, and crafts -._<br>
